For, in the opinion of several people working in palliative care, great moments take place at the very heart of this regression.
Patients entering the palliative care home Victor-Gadbois all suffer from cancer.
They have a life expectancy of up to three months.
At this stage, the team of doctors and nurses around them no longer provides "healing" care.
