According to tradition, people of different denominations leave them small words accompanied by prayers that are then answered.
Travel in height
Visit the ruins of the Massada fortress, a former enemy shelter built by Herod the Great in 25 B.C. for his family.
These ruins are located on steep rocks of a mountain 450 m above sea level.
Only mountaineers can go there by their own means.
For others, a cable car takes them to this summit full of history.
In the north of the country, between 1,600 and 2,040 m altitude, there is the ski resort of Mount Hermont, which welcomes many tourists in the winter.
A shuttle can take you there from the foot of the mountain.
The ski slopes make a total of 45 km long.
Old beliefs want pagan gods to have once lived on the top of the mountain.
