This country houses close to 300 museums.
It is impossible to visit them all during a single stay.
Here are the five most interesting ones that are really worth the detour.
First of all: the Museum of Israel located near the Knesset (Parliament).
It houses the very ancient manuscripts of Qumran, or manuscripts of the Dead Sea, discovered in the caves of the Desert of Judea, as well as nearly 500 miles of archaeological and anthropological objects.
See also: Museum of Art of Tel-Aviv.
The main paintings of Impressionists and Expressionists Monet, Pissarro, Renoir, Cézanne, Sisley, Matisse, Modigliani, Chagall and Picasso are shown there.
In Acre, the Hammam Al-Basha awaits you with its Turkish baths consisting of molds of visitors and supervisors of the time.
Once in Caesarea, enter the unique Private Ralli Museum where you can admire Rodin sculptures.
