From Friday evening to sunset on Saturday, markets, shops and public transport cease their activity.
And the week of work begins on Sunday morning.
Many cafés, restaurants and hotels serve only homemade food, which excludes pork, seafood, fish without scales and dishes composed of both milk and meat.
It offers a multitude of dishes based on lamb and beef, soups and desserts made from coconut milk but also the hops, traditional Jewish pasta, different sauces, dried peas balls, falafels, fruits and vegetables.
