It was a hard blow to the prestige of the United States, again aggravated later by the fiasco of the attempt to release hostages by force.
The diplomats kidnapped were finally released 444 days later, following negotiations organized by the Algerian government.
Their fate arouses a wave of solidarity and anti-Iranian sentiment in the United States.
The Iranian debacle strongly contributed to Jimmy Carter's defeat against Ronald Reagan in the 1980 presidential election.
