He rejoiced at the Vaqueros championship with Gaussa, but only remotely since in 1988 he was already the great manitou of the federation.
At that time, he preferred to take advantage of his duties and those of Mancy in the national team.
I remember when we first won it in the United States at the pre-Olympic tournament in Mexico City in 1989.
Then there was the 1990 World Cup, where we arrived 4th and where we should have won the bronze medal if this Canadian judge had not let us play the last game, Reyes said.
Is the 1990 World Team the best national team you've ever seen?
She's one of the best, just like the one who beat Dream Team at the 2004 Olympics.
